#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:5
msgid "Git configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:10
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:12
msgid ""
"Your personal git_ configurations are saved in the ``.gitconfig`` file in "
"your home directory. Here is an example ``.gitconfig`` file::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:16
msgid ""
"[user]\n"
"        name = Your Name\n"
"        email = you@yourdomain.example.com\n"
"\n"
"[alias]\n"
"        ci = commit -a\n"
"        co = checkout\n"
"        st = status -a\n"
"        stat = status -a\n"
"        br = branch\n"
"        wdiff = diff --color-words\n"
"\n"
"[core]\n"
"        editor = vim\n"
"\n"
"[merge]\n"
"        summary = true"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:34
msgid ""
"You can edit this file directly or you can use the ``git config --global`` "
"command::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:37
msgid ""
"git config --global user.name \"Your Name\"\n"
"git config --global user.email you@yourdomain.example.com\n"
"git config --global alias.ci \"commit -a\"\n"
"git config --global alias.co checkout\n"
"git config --global alias.st \"status -a\"\n"
"git config --global alias.stat \"status -a\"\n"
"git config --global alias.br branch\n"
"git config --global alias.wdiff \"diff --color-words\"\n"
"git config --global core.editor vim\n"
"git config --global merge.summary true"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:48
msgid ""
"To set up on another computer, you can copy your ``~/.gitconfig`` file, or "
"run the commands above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:52
msgid "In detail"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:55
msgid "user.name and user.email"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:57
msgid ""
"It is good practice to tell git_ who you are, for labeling any changes you "
"make to the code.  The simplest way to do this is from the command line::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:61
msgid ""
"git config --global user.name \"Your Name\"\n"
"git config --global user.email you@yourdomain.example.com"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:64
msgid ""
"This will write the settings into your git configuration file,  which should "
"now contain a user section with your name and email::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:67
msgid ""
"[user]\n"
"      name = Your Name\n"
"      email = you@yourdomain.example.com"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:71
msgid ""
"Of course you'll need to replace ``Your Name`` and ``you@yourdomain.example."
"com`` with your actual name and email address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:75
msgid "Aliases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:77
msgid "You might well benefit from some aliases to common commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:79
msgid ""
"For example, you might well want to be able to shorten ``git checkout`` to "
"``git co``.  Or you may want to alias ``git diff --color-words`` (which "
"gives a nicely formatted output of the diff) to ``git wdiff``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:83
msgid "The following ``git config --global`` commands::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:85
msgid ""
"git config --global alias.ci \"commit -a\"\n"
"git config --global alias.co checkout\n"
"git config --global alias.st \"status -a\"\n"
"git config --global alias.stat \"status -a\"\n"
"git config --global alias.br branch\n"
"git config --global alias.wdiff \"diff --color-words\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:92
msgid ""
"will create an ``alias`` section in your ``.gitconfig`` file with contents "
"like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:95
msgid ""
"[alias]\n"
"        ci = commit -a\n"
"        co = checkout\n"
"        st = status -a\n"
"        stat = status -a\n"
"        br = branch\n"
"        wdiff = diff --color-words"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:104
msgid "Editor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:106
msgid "You may also want to make sure that your editor of choice is used ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:108
msgid "git config --global core.editor vim"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:111
msgid "Merging"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:113
msgid "To enforce summaries when doing merges (``~/.gitconfig`` file again)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:115
msgid ""
"[merge]\n"
"   log = true"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:118
msgid "Or from the command line::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/configure_git.rst:120
msgid "git config --global merge.log true"
msgstr ""
